Example:
Input: [2, 3, 4, 5, 6]
Output: 30 (5 * 6)

```java
public class MaxProduct {
    public static int maxProduct(int[] nums) {
        int max1 = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
        int max2 = Integer.MIN_VALUE;

        for (int num : nums) {
            if (num > max1) {
                max2 = max1;
                max1 = num;
            } else if (num > max2) {
                max2 = num;
            }
        }

        return max1 * max2;
    }

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] nums = {2, 3, 4, 5, 6};
        System.out.println("Maximum product: " + maxProduct(nums));
    }
}
```

This solution iterates through the array once to find the two largest numbers. It then returns the product of these two numbers.

